     If you possess units within the current sector, information about
     each  of  the  individual troops will be shown, with two lines of
     information for each unit.  For armies, the information will con­
     tain the type of unit, the id number of the unit, the size of the
     unit, and the status and movement capabilities of the unit.   For
     navies,  the  id number of the fleet, the number of each class of
     ship within the fleet, and the status and  movement  capabilities
     of  the  unit will be shown.  And finally, the caravan units will
     have the size, id number, status and movement capabilities of the
     units  shown.  The currently selected unit within the sector will
     have a marker other than the `>' sign next to it.   Usually  this
     will  be  a  `*',  but  a `+' is used to indicate the leader of a
     group of army units or a ship or caravan which is carrying  items
     onboard.

     The above map shows all of the world which is visible to a nation
     "Aereol".  The currently selected sector is the  capital  located
     at  sector  [0,0] which is surrounded by a number of farming sec­
     tors.  There are a number of troops within the sector,  including
     the  nation  leaders  and Ruler, the "Wizard", which is currently
     selected.

